WEBVTT

00:02.370 --> 00:04.304
I'm just gonna run to the
store and get a few things.

00:04.306 --> 00:05.339
I'll pick you up
when you're done.

00:05.341 --> 00:06.790
Okay.

00:06.792 --> 00:09.665
I like it a little better
when you stay, but all right.

00:09.666 --> 00:10.864
Hey, Sheldon.

00:10.866 --> 00:12.700
Hello. I'm here for my haircut

00:12.702 --> 00:14.034
with Mr. D'Onofrio.

00:14.036 --> 00:15.970
I'm sorry, Uncle Tony's
in the hospital.

00:15.972 --> 00:17.171
He's pretty sick.

00:17.173 --> 00:21.008
Oh, dear, Mr. D'Onofrio's
in the hospital.

00:21.010 --> 00:23.578
Why do these things
always happen to me?

00:24.379 --> 00:25.563
I can cut it for you.

00:25.565 --> 00:27.448
You're not Mr. D'Onofrio.

00:28.267 --> 00:30.351
I get my hair cut
by Mr. D'Onofrio.

00:30.353 --> 00:31.652
You believe
this guy?

00:33.555 --> 00:34.888
Excuse us for a second.

00:34.890 --> 00:36.407
Sheldon, it's okay,
he can do it.

00:36.409 --> 00:37.525
He's a barber.

00:37.527 --> 00:40.328
He's not a barber,
he's the nephew.

00:40.330 --> 00:41.862
He's an example
of the kind

00:41.864 --> 00:45.166
of nepotism that runs rampant
in the barbering industry.

00:45.168 --> 00:46.834
Besides, Mr.
D'Onofrio knows

00:46.836 --> 00:49.403
exactly how I like my
hair done because he has

00:49.405 --> 00:52.607
all my haircut records
from my barber in Texas.

00:52.609 --> 00:54.408
What are you talking about?

00:54.410 --> 00:55.543
When I first
moved here,

00:55.545 --> 00:58.179
I was nervous about
finding a new barber,

00:58.181 --> 01:00.097
so my mother had all
my haircut records

01:00.099 --> 01:02.249
sent here to
Mr. D'Onofrio.

01:03.251 --> 01:06.721
There's no such thing
as haircut records.

01:06.723 --> 01:09.523
Yes, there are.

01:09.525 --> 01:10.725
Have you ever seen them?

01:10.727 --> 01:13.294
No, but my mother assured
me they were sent here,

01:13.296 --> 01:15.112
and I'll bet you
dollars to donuts

01:15.114 --> 01:16.714
that this one
doesn't have them.

01:17.282 --> 01:18.549
Uh, excuse me.

01:18.551 --> 01:21.152
Do you have access
to my haircut records?

01:21.154 --> 01:22.787
Your what?

01:22.789 --> 01:24.605
To paraphrase T.S. Eliot,

01:24.607 --> 01:26.123
this is the way
the world ends--

01:26.125 --> 01:29.126
not with a bang
but with a nephew.

01:30.329 --> 01:33.381
Sheldon, you're a grown man,
he's a professional,

01:33.383 --> 01:37.301
and your haircut is number three
on that poster from 1946.

01:37.303 --> 01:39.119
Just sit down

01:39.121 --> 01:40.137
and let him do it.

01:40.139 --> 01:41.789
Fine, but if I come
out of this

01:41.791 --> 01:43.774
looking like a dork,
it's on you.

01:45.000 --> 01:51.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:52.485 --> 01:54.185
So my kid said
the funniest thing today.

01:54.187 --> 01:55.269
Nope.

01:59.324 --> 02:01.659
When you tell this story later,

02:01.661 --> 02:05.079
the word we usually use is
"quirky."

02:05.081 --> 02:08.449
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

02:08.451 --> 02:12.036
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

02:12.038 --> 02:13.604
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

02:13.606 --> 02:16.090
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

02:16.092 --> 02:18.759
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

02:18.761 --> 02:21.479
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

02:21.481 --> 02:23.381
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

02:23.383 --> 02:24.380
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

02:24.381 --> 02:28.381
